msContents.summary: Medical commentaries, one on the aphorisms of Hippocrates and one on the Questions on medicine for students by Ḥunayn ibn Isḥāq, also known as Joannitius. The manuscript is lacking its beginning, and several pages at the beginning and end have been repaired.

msItem.title: Sharḥ Fuṣūl Buqurāṭ. Masāʼil Ḥunayn ibn Isḥāq.
شرح فصول بقراط. مسائل حنين بن اسحاق

author.persName: Ibn Abī Ṣādiq al-Nīsābūrī, Abū al-Qāsim ʻAbd al-Raḥmān ibn ʻAlī, -approximately 1068
ابن ابي صادق النيسابوري، ابو القاسم عبد الرحمن بن علي،

supportDesc.extent: 81 leaves : 250 x 162 (200 x 125) mm bound to 253 x 180 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (later) + 81; [1-81], modern foliation in pencil, upper left recto. Catchwords on each leaf, lower left verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh script in black ink; pointed.

binding.p: Later leather spine and corners, paper over boards.

origin.p: Item is undated, it was possibly copied in Mamluk Egypt or Syria in the 14th century.

history.provenance: Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, Nov. 2000.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2012.
